# Copy to compose/openclaw/.env before running task openclaw:up
# (this file is named .env.template per repo convention; root .gitignore
# negates it from the .env.* ignore rule so the template stays tracked
# while `.env` does not.)
#
# Variables consumed by compose/openclaw/compose.yml.

# --- Anthropic / OpenAI API keys ---
# Required — the gateway's entrypoint refuses to start without them.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# --- Gateway auth ---
# The Control UI prompts for this token on first connect. Generate any
# random high-entropy string (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`); agents never
# see it — it only gates the browser-to-gateway pairing flow.
OPENCLAW_AUTH_TOKEN=

# --- GitHub App ---
# Used only by the git-sync sidecar (this compose stack) to mint
# installation tokens for cloning $GIT_REPO_URL over HTTPS. GHCR image
# pulls don't use this — packages are public.
# Required App permissions on this repo:
#   Contents: Read     (for git-sync)
#   Metadata: Read     (default; needed by most endpoints)
# The private key is read from the host path below; compose bind-mounts
# it into git-sync at /etc/github-app/private-key.pem (read-only).
# The GH Actions deploy workflow writes the PEM to /srv/aca/secrets/
# github-app.pem — that's the default path referenced below.
GITHUB_APP_ID=
GITHUB_APP_INSTALLATION_ID=
GITHUB_APP_PRIVATE_KEY_HOST_PATH=/srv/aca/secrets/github-app.pem

# Repo the git-sync sidecar keeps synced under /workspace/repo.
GIT_REPO_URL=https://github.com/ArchiCain/automated-coding-agent.git

# --- Optional overrides ---
# Branch the sidecar tracks (also used by the gateway's git identity).
OPENCLAW_GIT_BRANCH=dev
# GitHub App slug used to build the bot identity the gateway commits as.
OPENCLAW_GIT_APP_SLUG=scain-openclaw

# --- Host-specific ---
# Supplemental gid added to the gateway container so uid 1000 (`node`) can
# open /var/run/docker.sock. On host-machine (Ubuntu) the socket is
# root:docker 660, so set this to the docker group gid:
#   DOCKER_SOCKET_GID=$(getent group docker | cut -d: -f3)
DOCKER_SOCKET_GID=
